<subsection xml:id="subsec-velocity-and-acceleration">
    <title>Velocity and Acceleration in Different Situations</title>
    <p>
        <m>\textbf{Velocity}</m> is Speed in a specified direction or the rate of change of displacement with time.
    </p>
    <p>
        Velocity differs from speed as it includes direction.
    </p>
    <p>
        Symbol of velocity is given as <m>\textbf{v}</m> while speed is given as <m>\textbf{s}</m>
    </p>
    <p>
        <m> v = \frac{\textbf{d}}{\textbf{t}} </m>
    </p>
    <p>
        where <m>\textbf{d}</m> represents the distance and <m>\textbf{t}</m> represents time
    </p>
    <p>
        For motion with <m>\textbf{constant velocity}</m>, the equation is 
    </p>
    <p>
        <md>
            <mrow> \textbf{s = vt} </mrow>
        </md>
    </p>
    <p>
        where <m>\textbf{v}</m> is velocity , <m>\textbf{t}</m> is time and <m>\textbf{s}</m> is displacement
    </p>
    <p>
        <m>\textbf{Acceleration}</m> - The rate of change of velocity with time. The symbol is  <m>a</m> and SI unit is <m>m/s²</m>
    </p>
    <p>
        Acceleration is given by
    </p>
    <p>
        <md>
            <mrow>\textbf{Acceleration} \, = \frac{\textbf{Change in velocity}}{\textbf{Time Taken}} </mrow>
        </md>
    </p>
    <p>
        <md>
            <mrow> a = \frac{\Delta v}{\Delta t} </mrow>
        </md>
    </p>
    <p>
        
    </p>
    <p>
        Negative acceleration is called <m>\textbf{ ( deceleration or retardation)}</m>
    </p>
    <p>
        For motion with <m>\textbf{constant acceleration}</m>, the three equations of motion are:
    </p>
    <p>
        <ol marker="i).">
            <li>
                <p>
                    <m>\textbf{final velocity}</m> = Initial velocity + (acceleration <m> \times </m> time)
                </p>
                <p>
                    <m> v = u + at </m>
                </p>
                <p> where;
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                <m>\textbf{v}</m> is Final velocity
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                <m>\textbf{u}</m> is initial velocity
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                <m>\textbf{a}</m> is acceleration
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                <m>\textbf{t}</m> is time
                            </p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </p>
            </li> 
            <li>    
                <p>
                    <m>\textbf{Displacement}</m> = <m>(\text{initial velocity} \times \text{time}) + (\frac{1}{2} \times \text{acceleration} \times \text{time}^2) </m>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <m> s = ut + \frac{1}{2} at^2 </m>
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>    
                
                <p>
                    <m>\textbf{Final velocity}^2</m> = <m>\text{Initial velocity}^2</m> + (2 <m>\times</m> acceleration <m>\times</m> displacement)
                </p>
                <p>
                    <m>\textbf{v}^2 = \textbf{u}^2 + \, (2 \times \textbf{acceleration}) \times \textbf{s}^2</m>
                </p>
            </li>
        </ol>
    </p>
    <activity>
        <p>
            <m>{\color{black} \textbf{Work in groups}}</m>
        </p>
        <p>
            A car accelerates from <m>\textbf{75 km/h}</m> to <m>\textbf{90 km/h}</m> in <m>\textbf{10 seconds}</m>
        </p>
        <p>
            Find it's acceleration
        </p>
        
    </activity>
     <example>
        <statement>
            <p>
                A car starts from rest and accelerates at 2 m/s² for 5 seconds. Find its final velocity.
            </p>
        </statement>    
        <solution>
            <p>
                <m> v = u + at  </m>
            </p>  
            <p>
                <m>= 0 + (2 \times 5) = 10 \textbf{ m/s}</m>
            </p> 
            <p>
                The final velocity is <m>10 \textbf{ m/s}</m>
            </p>
        </solution>
    </example>
    <example>
        <statement>
            <p>
                A rocket accelerates from rest to <m>\textbf{250 m/s in 10 seconds}</m>. Calculate the rocket's acceleration.
            </p>
        </statement>
        <solution>
            <p>
                Initial velocity  <m>\textbf{(u) = 0 m/s}</m>
            </p>
            <p>
                Final velocity  <m>\textbf{(v) = 250 m/s}</m>
            </p>
            <p>
                Time (t) = <m>\textbf{10 seconds}</m>
            </p>
            <p>
                Acceleration (a) = (v - u) / t
                <md>
                    <mrow> \frac{\textbf{(v - u)}}{\texbf{t}} </mrow>
                </md>
            </p>
            <p>
                <md>
                    <mrow> a = \frac{\textbf{(250 m/s - 0 m/s)}}{\textbf{10 seconds}} </mrow>
                </md>
            </p>
            <p>
                <md>
                    <mrow> a = \frac{\textbf{(250 m/s)}}{\textbf{10 seconds}}</mrow>
                </md>
            </p>
            <p>
                <md>
                    <mrow>\textbf{ a = 25 m/s²}</mrow>
                </md>
            </p>
            <p>
                The rocket's acceleration is <m>\textbf{25 m/s²}</m>
            </p>
        </solution>
    </example>
    <example>
        <statement>
            <p>
                An object decelerates from 20 m/s to 5 m/s in 3 seconds. What is its acceleration?
            </p>
        </statement>
        <solution>
            <p>
                Initial velocity  <m>\textbf{(u) = 20 m/s}</m>
            </p>
            <p>
                Final velocity  <m>\textbf{(v) = 5 m/s}</m>
            </p>
            <p>
                Time (t) = <m>\textbf{3 seconds}</m>
            </p>
            <p>
                Acceleration (a) = (v - u) / t
                <md>
                    <mrow> \frac{\textbf{(v - u)}}{t} </mrow>
                </md>
            </p>
            <p>
                <md>
                    <mrow> a = \frac{\textbf{(5 m/s - 20 m/s)}}{\textbf{3 seconds}} </mrow>
                </md>
            </p>
            <p>
                <md>
                    <mrow> a = \frac{\textbf{(-15 m/s)}}{\textbf{3 seconds}}</mrow>
                </md>
            </p>
            <p>
                <md>
                    <mrow>\textbf{ a = - m/s²}</mrow>
                </md>
            </p>
            <p>
                The object's acceleration is  <m>\textbf{ -5 m/s²}</m>. The negative sign indicates deceleration (slowing down).
            </p>
        </solution>
    </example>
